# 7: Penalized Spline Term

## 7a Construct model
We can constuct penalized splines within `gam()` 

Default is 10 knots

Only increase if need >~8.5 edf (with 10 knots our maximum edf is ~8.5) (edf = estimated degrees of freedom, vs. user-defined)

Penalty is estimated -- the model dplyr::selects the penalty that leads to the highest gcv

```{r}
mod.ps <- gam(AveBMI ~ s(AvePM) + FemaleUnemp + MaleUnemp + LTHS + 
                MedHInc + MedHVal + PerBlack + PerLatinx + PerAsianAm +
                ClimateRegion, data = df)
```

## 7b Model Summary
This model prevents overfitting by applying a penalty to excessive curvature.

```{r}
summary(mod.ps)
```
## 7c Extract Penalty
this is the penalty estimated by the model
The higher the value, the greater the penalty, meaning the spline is being
smoothed more (i.e., less wiggly).

```{r}
mod.ps$sp
```
## 7d Model Plot

`plot.gam` offers a nice default plot 

A quick way to plot the change in predicted AveBMI with AvePM

